Reasoning: The paper deals with a wireless switching framework using beamforming and linear detection, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of a MIMO switch also involves multiple antennas and signal processing, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses scheduling and optimization for fair switching, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY).
